2022 couldn’t have been what it was if not for family. thankful for friends turned family; platonic, romantic & friends turned family that made every single day feel like love🤎

tbh i’ve always loved our lil nuclear family of 4 (mama tek, papa tek, brother tek & myself) & we’re really so rich in love/friendship, but as an immigrant who’s larger family is spread out across the globe, i always used to look at my friends with larger families and wish I had that on the holidays. the loudness, the fun, the chaos, etc.. & for the first time in a long time, all of the atekus in the US were able to get together & celebrate the holidays together with our beautiful other friends turned family 🥹 i really couldn’t of imagined a better/more blessed way to spend time with people that I love & really am just thankful that i get to experience moments like these in this life.

it’s beautiful to know that whatever nonsense or blessings 2023 brings, i’m/we’re/YOU are not alone! to the best year ever bc regardless of what comes, i’m the most blessed to experience a love like this. 🥂

the end of an era (for now) 🎤✨ 

vulnerable moment so be gentle w me but i was recently laid off along with so many other talented folks in media rn. i’m so proud of the stories i covered, homies I got to put on + convos I was able to have w my faves; i can rlly say the past few years have been the most fun working w the dopest people @complex & i look forward to crossing paths with them again 🖤 life is rlly so unpredictable rn, so I feel for all the homies across all industries that have been affected by layoffs🙏🏿 

nevertheless im excited for what’s next so cheers to the blessings that are already otw 💫🥂🆙 

p.s. i still have so much archived work content that I never posted bc #busy so when you see it go up like it/love it/comment on it & don’t ask no questions cause now ya know 😂 ty in advance x

pretty little thing💘 

when I moved to LA in 2018, @wme/ @endeavor was my 1st real “big girl job.” I was there for 3 years doing my lil 9-5,  while somehow (& very psychotically) doing content creation, freelance production & storytelling after & on the weekends — clearly the grind’s always been real 🧟‍♀️😵‍💫 

at the same time i also got to work with @amplifyafrica to takeover coachella, co-host a podcast, + other projects so it was bittersweet to make a return to lala land to celebrate african excellence w both of them after so much change, elevation, & growth✨

mama tek always says ‘when ya look good ya feel good’ & I absolutely needed to feel good/confident for my first speaking engagement since well, atp y’all know by now 🤣 so ofc I pulled up to @tsmgofashionrental to get the guidance of my fave stylist/fashion girly @baldwinwearsblack who was so patient as i defined my personal style (lol) & got me all the way together with the pieces that i felt most comfortable to show up n show out in 💁🏿‍♀️👗🥰👢

stay tuned for part 2 to see the final lewkkkkkk 😘
